 Hafiz Bello: Birnin Kebbi Governor Abubakar Atiku Abubakar of Kebbi State has commenced his next level agenda with the health sector byÂ partnering with the International Islamic Relief Organisation (IIRO) to carry out 1000 free eye surgeries for indigenes of the state. According to Dr Muhammad Ahmad Muhammad Altayeh the IRRO Health Coordinator, screening will be carried out by Kebbi State health officials from 25th April, 2019 at the Kalgo Medical Centre whilst their team will commence the Surgical operations on 30th of April, 2019. He thanked the wife of the governor Dr Zainab Bagudu and her Medicaid Foundation for facilitating the entire process and ensuring the success of the program. The health coordinator who led a pre inspection team to Kebbi State this weekend further stated that 1000 prescription glasses and medication for 6 months will be provided FREE. The state government will also provide security, meals, transportation, and accommodation for all the patients and workers throughout the duration of the programme. For more information and to register patients please contact Your Local Government Health coordinator. Patients can also be registered and screened at Medicaid Radiodiagnostic Centre Birnin Kebbi from 26th April from 3-5pm daily. Kebbi State  Suleiman idris is a graduate of Fed Univ of Tech Minna (BTECH Mathematics/Comp Science), Specialist in ICT Support Services. also proficient in use of  online journalism tools & Social media management.  I currently serve as I.T Officer with Africa's Largest TV Network NTA